etymologies: mid 19th century; earliest use found in State Capital Reporter (Concord, New Hampshire). Apparently an arbitrary formation, probably influenced by whang or whang and doodle

notes.text: Chiefly in fantastical or nonsensical contexts.

definitions: A person or thing whose name one cannot remember, does not know, or does not wish to mention.
Also rangdoodle. In draw poker: a round in which the stakes or betting limits are raised, typically after a big hand has been shown.
